Sentencas: An anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with a thin Gd(0.1)Ce(0.9)O(1.95) (GDC) electrolyte film of 3 mu m in thickness and nanostructured La(0.8)Sr(0.2)Co(0.8)Fe(0.2)O(3) (LSCF) cathode showed high electrochemical performance at low operating temperatures, with a maximum power density of 0.99 W cm(-2) at 600 degrees C using hydrogen as fuel.
Titulo: High performance anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell based on thin-film electrolyte and nanostructured cathode
